# nullprobe Workflow

## Namespace Protection

This project supports multiple AI environments in parallel:
- `.claude/` — Claude Code agents, skills, commands
- `.cursor/` — Cursor rules and MCP config
- `.agent/` — Antigravity/Gemini CLI rules and MCP config

When working from Cursor, prefer not to edit `.claude/` or `.agent/` unless intentionally updating shared protocols.

## Session Start

Read `docs/CONTEXT.md` first — current status, what works, recent changes. Update "Recent changes" after substantive work.

## Shared Source of Truth

- `AI_FRAMEWORK.md` — portable AI collaboration guide (authoritative)
- `wiki/index.md` — knowledge catalog (read at session start)
- `wiki/log.md` — session log (append after substantive work)

## MCP Alignment

Keep MCP servers in sync across:
- Claude Code: `.mcp.json`
- Cursor: `.cursor/mcp.json`
- Antigravity: `.agent/mcp_config.json`

## Before Finishing Work

- Run `npm run build` to verify TypeScript compiles
- Append to `wiki/log.md` if you learned something durable
- Update `wiki/index.md` if you created new architecture decisions

## Core Principle

This tool is lightweight above all else. Every feature addition must pass:
"Does this make the tool simpler to use, or more complex?"
